abstract: Health leaders in Washington State have been working to monitor at least 16 people who may have been in close contact with the man who flew in from China.
lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Health officials scrambled on Wednesday to contact more than a dozen people who may have been exposed to the United States’ first case of the Wuhan coronavirus, even as regulators sought to assure the public there was little risk from an illness that has rapidly spread across Asia, killing at least 17 people.
